>Are you talking about the heater boxes.  The manifolds radiate heat for
>heating the cabin.  The "metal wrapping" is part of the ductwork.  If
>you don't need heat you can replace the whole thing with a "J" pipe.  If
>you want heat you need to replace the rusted out box. And get the
>ductwork all intact.
